From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chainguard <noreply@chainguard.dev>
Date: Tue, 25 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] fix boringssl OPENSSL_memchr const qualifier discard

GCC 13 treats discarding const qualifiers as an error
(-Werror=discarded-qualifiers). The C-path OPENSSL_memchr in
src/crypto/internal.h takes `const void *s` but returns `void *`,
and passes `s` directly to memchr() whose return type is `void *`.
GCC 13 flags this as discarding the const qualifier from the pointer
target type.

Use patch_cmds in the boringssl http_archive to add an explicit
(void *) cast, avoiding Bazel's unreliable nested-patch mechanism.

---
 WORKSPACE | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/WORKSPACE b/WORKSPACE
--- a/WORKSPACE
+++ b/WORKSPACE
@@ -53,6 +53,9 @@
     urls = [
         "https://github.com/google/boringssl/archive/38314c88e85527ffc4ae0a7f642b6fd39777e0a9.tar.gz",
     ],
+    patch_cmds = [
+        "sed -i 's/return memchr(s, c, n);/return (void *)memchr(s, c, n);/' src/crypto/internal.h",
+    ],
 )

 http_archive(
